Linux
/etc/resolv.conf  <-- DNS servers that the system uses for name resolution are defined in the /etc/resolv. conf file
/etc/hosts        <-- translate hostnames or domain names to IP addresses
/etc/crontab      <-- to schedule 
/etc/fstab        <--contains information about major filesystems on the system
~/.bashrc         <--script file that's executed when a user logs in
~/.bash_logout    
~/.bash_profile   <-- export path
/etc/profile and /etc/profile.d/*.sh are the global initialization scripts that are equivalent to ~/.profile for each user
/etc/environment
~/.bash_history   <-- history of user activities
Rsyslog

git
.gitignore        <--  A gitignore file specifies intentionally untracked files that Git should ignore, .gitignore file must be edited and committed by hand when you have new files that you wish to ignore.
